@BlueScalyCool 

Well in fairness, for a strategy RPG of this scale with that many characters, giving a personality to each and every one of them would make for an overloaded story. it's enough to give them motivation to join.
Look at newer games like Disgaea, you simply construct your fighters. No motivation at all.

@BlueScalyCool 
Well if you think about it...the characters in SF2 had no development at all, the story was fairly basic by Ps2 standards (it was a cut above what we were used to for Genesis games) and concept...not sure how to answer that one.

SF2 has a lot of nostalgia value for people, I guess. Me included, it was my first SJRPG and I freakin love it even now.
